This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with training large-scale kernelized support vector machines using stochastic gradient descent. Additionally, it may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as SVMs are commonly used in AI applications. The paper also mentions the use of SVMs in computer vision (cs.CV) and data science (cs.DS) applications. Finally, the paper discusses the use of budgeted stochastic gradient descent, which is a technique commonly used in neural networks (cs.NE).
